 that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William Francklyn was born in 1435, in Wiltshire, England, his father, Robert Francklyn, was 20 and his mother, Isabel St. John, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Ann Babe Smith. He died in 1500, in his hometown, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1435–1500":"1435–1500","1435–1485":"1435–1485","1458–1520":"1458–1520","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1410–1437":"1410–1437","1437":"1437","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1444":"1444","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1520":"1520","1485":"1485","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1435–1500":"1435–1500","1435–1485":"1435–1485","1458–1520":"1458–1520","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1410–1437":"1410–1437","1437":"1437","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1444":"1444","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1520":"1520","1485":"1485","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire,England":"Wiltsh